,Recommended,227480,9655413,"Posted: 28 March, 2014",all,Scotth3n,"Honestly, I feel like this game's reviews are unfair. Sure, it's a little brainless at times, but that's why I love it. I only paid 2 dollars, but I feel like the normal 10 dollar asking price is still more than fair. The graphics are great, the gameplay is enjoyable, and it just reminds me of classic shooters where story didn't matter and you could have a blast just tearing enemies apart with friends. The customization isn't incredibly deep, but still respectable. You can choose between different face and outfit cominations, and there is a nice selection of unlockable weapons (all with multiple upgrades that also change appearance). I've purchased numerous AAA titles in the past few months and this game has already kept my interest longer than any of them. Anyone who puts this game down, especially for the price, simply can't handle the difficulty/play style- which is fine but that doesn't merit a bad review. Anyway, just round up some friends, grab some beer, and have a ball blowing demons into tiny bits."
,Recommended,227480,11592711,"Posted: 7 August, 2014",all,AKatarzynaK,"In God Mode you play as a descendant of an ancient Greek god who is forced to battle hordes of creatures brought forth by Hades. There are five maps in which you can test your skills, each is vastly different and beautifully designed.For every area you enter you will be given a trial to complete. You will be unable to enter the next level of the map until you have completed the trail at hand. These trails vary greatly and range from things designed to make gameplay more challenging such as lowering your maximum health, to more amusing things such as making all of your enemies wear silly tophats.Combat is fun and faced paced as you will continuously find yourself surrounded by enemies. There is a wide variety of weapons which you can earn and upgrade as well as different abilities which you can choose from.In order to make the game more challenging you are able to choose between different levels of difficulty. There are also different handicaps called Oaths which you can turn on at the beginning of a map to give yourself more of a challenge and earn more gold/XP.Some of the reviews for this game seem to be taking it a little too seriously. If you buy this expecting a well polished top notch shooter you will be sorely disappointed. I got this game on sale for $2.00 and feel this was a great price for the how much entertainment it has provided. Well worth the purchase if you’re in the mood for some mindless fun, have a fondness for Greek architecture/♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ized mythology, and have a friend or two to play with."
,Recommended,227480,12394443,"Posted: 6 October, 2014",all,Mizz Marieee,I'm so lonely in this empty world... I wish I had someone to play with...
,Not Recommended,227480,6820269,"Posted: 18 June, 2013",all,Bastion,"I had some fun with this game, but you might not. Let me explain why. So, before you buy, have this in consideration and make sure you're ok with the following:- You have to wait to have fun. Some weapons are more enjoyable than others. But the game has level requirement for upgrades and weapons. This means that you have to put a couple hours on the game before you get to full potential and get to experiment with all the weapons to figure it out which ones you want to use. After that, yeah chances are you will have fun with the game.- The Oaths system (you can get xp and gold bonus at the cost of some penalty like less damage, less health..etc) and the test of faith mechanics (conditions that affect parts of the map and are different each time you play) allow some gameplay customization and some variety.- Play co-op. This game was not made to singleplayer. Old School Games didn't even bother to escalate the number of monsters if you play solo. Of course you can go trough a map playing solo, but what's really the point if you'll beat the same map 3x faster playing with some people?- You probably will have to go on forums look for people to play with you. Let's be honest, not a crazy amount of people plays this game. There's an in-game matchmaking system, but you will probably spend a lot of time looking for players without succeeding. Your best bet is look on the forums where there's usually some players that will happily play with you, regardless of your skill level. You can avoid all this if you have friends you know well that are willing to play with you. But either way, the point i'm trying to make is: you will depend on other people to play this game.-Old School Games is not a great dev team, to say the least. This game had a tons of bugs, some of them avoided people to even play the game. Some of these bugs were VERY SLOWLY fixed, but some of them remain to this very day, still affecting some players. And you know what's best? While people were trying to get the game to work, Old School Games released ""R.I.P.D.: The Game"". You know what that game is? God Mode re-skinned. Old School Game attitude to me is a: ""We have players that can't play our game? ♥♥♥♥ them. We need more money, so let's try to not fix our game, let's be worried in re-skin it to sell it again."". And you know what's even better? R.I.P.D. had some of the EXACT SAME BUGS of God Mode. Seems like a joke, right? Yeah...So, if you are ok with all the above and you still wanna buy the game, go ahead. I'm not judging you. But if any of what i said above remotely bothers you and you think it will ruin your experience, don't."
,Not Recommended,227480,33151783,Posted: 2 July,all,Tokoo,"I really want to recommend this one, but unfortunately if you do not have friends to play with this game is either going to boring, or become frustrating. The Greek Mythology lore is the thing that brought me to this game, but after buying I quickly found out that it was a mistake.Don’t get me wrong the game itself is really great, loads of fun to be honest. The main problems are that the developers disappeared after releasing this game, so there hasn’t been any updates, or fixes in like 3 or 4 years. Again it’s multiplayer only so like most games coming out now days with the “Multiplayer Only” tag die quickly when they are not well known titles. Unfortunately, you will be in que for a game for an hour plus, if you even find a match, and for some odd reason this game doesn’t have a way to browse for a server which would fix the problem altogether.Yes, you can just play solo games, but you will find out quickly this game can become quite challenging even with a group, let along solo. On the forum’s you might be able to find a few people that will partner up with you, but to be honest it’s a lot of headache, considering that this game is really grindy, which is turn off for a lot of people as well.Pro’sGraphic are pretty decent considering how long ago this was made.Voice acting is solid, quite funny as well, if you like corny humor.Gameplay is a blast if you have people to play with.Challenging this game can be.Lots, and lots of customization.Con’sMatch making is almost non-existent.Lots of griding, and I mean lots.Developers are gone.If you still want to play this, I recommend buying on sale for a couple of dollars, but without a few friends that will play it with you, I wouldn’t advise buying it at all."
