,Not Recommended,227480,29773971,Posted: 7 February,all,Ov3RT4K3R,"God Mode is a four-player horde third person shooter with non-linear gameplay that can also be played alone.The plot is that you and your teammates must blast their way through the Maze of Hades and its demonic denizens using an arsenal of firearm weaponry and deity inspired magical 'special attacks' in order to avoid eternal damnation.Enemies are not the brightest, however their overwhelming numbers will be dangerous.There are five levels, all simple but beautiful in design.You can earn gold which can be spent on upgrading your weapons' usefulness, getting new ones, and buying extra powers and outfits for your character. Many of the purchases are locked until you reach a certain level, which serves as the primary motivation to keep on playing.The graphics are not surprising however are not bad.God Mode is getting boring really fast due to lack of variety and also it might be hard nowadays to get a game with other players as the game community is more or less dead.Better go for games like Killing Floor or Left 4 Dead.Sounds 5/10Graphics 5/10Gameplay 5/10Atmosphere 4/10If you liked my review, please feel free to follow me and/or my curator group:http://steamcommunity.com/id/Ov3RT4K3R/myworkshopfiles/?section=guideshttp://steamcommunity.com/groups/orcollective#curationAlso feel free to check out my YouTube Channel:https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC83DYCmrWfl9ttrhX54jmWA"
