,Not Recommended,227480,428394,"Posted: 29 August, 2013",all,｢C❤A｣ Pocahawtness,"God Mode is close to being a really fun game to play. The basic concept is similar to Killing Floor. You have a relatively small map in which monsters appear and you and your team have to fight them off. Simple as that really. You spend most of your time running from them, trying to kill them until there are none left. A problem with this is that you don’t seem to be able to run very fast and there's a noticeable delay between hitting run and it actually running! Combined with no jump or crouch, you feel very slow and limited in movement. Rather odd for a game that obviously needs a lot a fast fluid movement. Also, you can’t shoot and run at the same time, which is really problematic at times. Add to this the weapon sounds aren’t great and all in all you have pretty unconvincing movement and sound. It’s a shame really, because I think just a few small changes to the game would greatly improve it. But hey, at it’s current price BUY IT and judge for yourself!"
