,Recommended,227480,10917445,"Posted: 28 June, 2014",all,GRRRR,"Actually pretty well made. Graphics are good, music is ok, no technical problems (except for not being able to bind the left/right arrow - fixed with a little external rebind program but still).Its basically any games Horde mode, or for those who still remember, UT Rpg Invasion. You progress through a series of arenas by killing everything, collecting ammo, armor and health strewn about. A little twist on the formula is that each arena can have a random beneficial or harmful or neutral effect like infinite ammo or tougher enemies or just everybody wearing a hat. You get xp and gold, you unlock new weapons and their upgrades (damage etc) with higher levels and then purchase them.The big fat problem is the lasting appeal. Coop makes everything better and again, its  really very well made but i couldnt imagine milking more than a few hours out of this replaying the same five (decently big, granted) maps over and over with increasingly bulletspongy enemies.Less than two euro for about 3 hours of entertainment so im not complaining, however Serious Sam or Painkiller or heck, Mass Effect 3 MP provides the same with more variation."
