,Recommended,227480,9948919,"Posted: 27 April, 2014",all,L. F. Antrider,"RATING: 5/10This is a purely splay and flay 3rd person shooter.  It is worth getting if you like 3rd person shooters.The atmosphere is very hellish (which apparently looks like Ancient Greece).  The graphics are great, though.In this game there is no time to strategize, hardly time to aim, and you will often get obliterated unless you're playing with some friends who are packing some heavy heat.The weapons are fun... The monsters are gnarly and neat, although not varied between the different maps.  Unfortunately there are only about 6 maps, which after awhile can get a little old.In the game description on the store page, I think the RPG/looting elements of this game were over-sold.  There are truly not that many customization options for skins compared to the awesome designs the developers could have come up with.  Also,  no promise of any more additional content coming in the future.  Also, it doesn't take very long to hit the XP/lvl cap and upgrade all your gear, at which point there is no need to loot anything at all because there are no consumables to purchase.  The abilities are universal across the board for players and really don't play into any game tactics at all, nor do they really add much to the characters.As far as unique gameplay, each map you play has various challenges you must complete to get through the lvl.  There are only about 10-15 different challenges, but they are randomly selected each map which adds a nice layer of difficulty and mixes things up a bit.THE BIGGEST PROBLEM WITH THIS GAME:  It is a multi-player game that has the SH*TTIEST F*CKING multi- matchmaking system ever.  You will wait for hours to find another person by clicking ""quick match"".  You literally start to hear crickets after awhile.  However, there is a way around this.  Namely, go to the forums, find the thread titled GODMODE KONNECT by moi and add a bunch of friends who play God Mode.  Once in awhile I get a match going with a few good people.  This game can have potential to be fun solo too, though.... that is if you have some large cajones.Overall, this game needs more costumes, more unique abilities, and possibly some consumable items to purchase, and a better frackin multi-player setup.  It is, however, a nice little digression from more serious games.  So take a serious look at getting this game!  (When it's on sale for 2.50)."
