,Not Recommended,227480,10033793,"Posted: 6 May, 2014",all,CorvusCorax,"I think God Mode is an original game. I like the concept of riddling creatures from the Greek mythology with bullets. The graphics are decent and although the game only has a few levels some of them look gorgeous.This is a typical multiplayer shooter: you fight against waves of enemies and the further you progress on the level the tougher encounters you have. Eventually, there is a boss but not every level has a final countdown in this form. You collect XP in order to level up and upon completion of a level you can pick up a lot of gold coins enabling you to purchase upgrades for your weapons and even to customise your character by buying various types of clothing.God Mode is nothing special but the mythology here makes the shooter an interesting game albeit it still remains a bit mediocre.I do not recommend it for the same reason I did not recommend the two Sniper Elite Zombie Army games: finding a host is impossible! In fact, even if you are the host you can spend eons until someone joins. And do bear in mind that there is a community willing to play this game even 1 year after its release.So, if you have friends who are just as eager to play this game as you are do team up with them and unleash your fury on titans, cyclops, skeletons and any other mythical creatures you encounter. Otherwise avoid it if you can."
