,Recommended,227480,7334771,"Posted: 7 October, 2013",all,Vash(88),"ARCADE SHOOTER.... Simple as that.  In this game, your objective is to shoot every single thing that moves. And at times that even means your buddies!Every player  will unlock the same weapons at the same levels, as well as the costumes.  The way a  person spends his or her  skills points can be vastly different, however.   Some people might choose the heavy weapons that slow the player down, and have a dps ability on the side.   Others might use a lighter build with the ability to run around and heal his or her teammates.   The fact that each weapon and skill can be leveled separately adds a lot to the variety of the builds.   A fun stand alone addition to the game is a bonus round that the team is given after finishing a level.  The players are placed in a small room with loot piles that spawn randomly during a given time limit -- friendly fire is turned on!  Some of the best moment of the game were during the loot grinds xDUnfortunately, the two downfalls are  the lack of maps and bosses, and the visual lag when not hosting.   The lack of maps and bosses can make unlocking the higher level gear and skills a grind after a short time.  The visual lag isn't much of a problem on the first two difficulty levels; however, once the head count goes up with the difficulty setting, and the damage being dealt increases along with it, the story changes.Over all it is a fun game with a modest price tag.   Be sure to let me know if you get it."
