,Recommended,227480,17310194,"Posted: 30 July, 2015",all,Natendragon,"Alright, so I have limited gameplay as of right now. However, I do expect to play this game more and more as my life permits.God Mode is an arena styled creature shooter. The map is essentially an arena, with health, armor and ammo pickups. You start the match in a lmited area, and once cleared, are allowed access to the next area, not being able to turn back. It's fun in that every sub-area, there is an altar that provides a game modifier, whether it helps you or it helps the monsters. Nothing that completely screws you over, but gives the round that extra oomph. If you die too many times (I believe the number is 4), the game is over. You gain experience and gain occasional gold drops through killing monsters. The bigger the monster, the larger the experience payout. There is a nice variety of monsters and undead to kill, forcing you to analyze and figure out what to kill first. At the end of each of the ""mazes"" (maps), there is a boss. Nothing too overkill, but then again I'm playing on ""Bronze"" difficult (easy). Guns are upgradeable, so that when you lose a match, you can upgrade your arsenal and get further than you did before. It's a grind game. Lots of killing is require to level up, plus guns and upgrades cost a fortune. After nearly an hour and a half, I amassed around 20,000 gold, just to be met with the first gun upgrades costing 10,000 each.The only real downside I have found so far is that Matchmaking is nearly impossible. I sat in the automated matchmaking screen for a good 10 minutes, just to have two people pop in, who left within 10 seconds. You're going to play solo unless you pair up with your friends. There are other flaws in this game that don't really bother me, but honestly you have to go in with no expectation for this game. Just anticipate that you'll have fun shooting and killing a lot of monsters.TL;DR: Fun game, worth the $3 I paid. It's a grind game. Limited maps, impossible matchmaking. Shoot monsters for hours on end."
76561198076453018,Recommended,227480,17190179,"Posted: 23 July, 2015",all,NorthernLights8,Its a mindless grindfest with 4-5 levels but it adds elements you don't see to often in todays games. If you realize this is what it is going in you will be happy with you purchase. I recommend getting it on sale.I have two cons with the game. One is that there is no local coop that would make the game so much better. Two is that it is a bit buggy not unplayable by any means. The only major issue I've had bug wise was during one of my runs the enemies glitched out and I wasn't able to finish the level and move on so I had to quit. Quitting still nets you all your experience and gold so it wasn't the biggest loss in the world.In the end I have really enjoyed this game just realize what you are getting yourself into beforehand.
