,Recommended,227480,11006595,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,HGArchis,"Rating: 5/10Not sure if I should be recommending this game or not, but this game sure is good fun when it comes to short plays. Sure, it's an epic grind fest where all you do is kill enemies upon enemies in 5 different locations. Of course this would be torture if you are to play this game for a couple of hours at a stretch. However if you hunger for challenge, and that without having to put much stress to your brains - This is the game for you. This game is perfect if you enjoy taking breaks between 2 good games by playing short round/level based games like Tetris, Street Fighter, Pac Man, etc. This is just customized for masochistic gamers. However this game does have some fun elements to it, if you don't look at it as a resource for tedium. There are plenty of customizations, weapons and enemy types. The in-game modifiers or the so called ""Tests of Faith"" do bring some excitement to the gameplay. The graphics are decent and the game is set around Ancient Greek Mythology which brings in some diversity. Overall not a must buy, but if you want to throw away a few bucks and can't think of anything better, buy it."
