,Recommended,227480,4211326,"Posted: 31 August, 2013",all,核 Nuclear,"God Mode is a cooperative arena PVE shoot em up game. First and foremost, it is noted that this particular game is indeed a budget title so not much should be expected as we expect from an AAA game. If you play this game by yourself, you're going to have a bad time.God Mode is more for playing with your friends because the long matchmaking will have you pulling out your hair and sacrificing your first-born to Saxton Hale to fix it. If you happen to be LUCKY enough to get in a full lobby the game has a high probability to crash. Within 6 hours of me playing this game, it has crashed at least twice. However, when you play the full experience without any problems it is worth SOME of the trouble. It is priced at $10 and it's a little bit pricey in my opinion for what it offers. It has a variety of guns and they are NOT reskins. When you upgrade the guns the aesthetics of the weapon also change. Want to use a rail gun as a primary with a mini-gun as a secondary? Go right ahead. You can even customize your character but don't expect Saints Row level of customization. There is ""abilities"" your character can use such as healing aura, shield, etc. Each battle is different from the last because it has a randomized event each time so one battle you might fight giant enemies, the next battle might have one shot kills (this counts for you as well). The announcer is a nice touch but after a few minutes in I just muted the game because the soundtrack is not worth mentioning nor is the announcer.Rating: 5/10 (Average game)It's simplicity gives it accessibility from anyone and everyone but that is also it's drawback. For $10 it might be a bit much, but it can easily offer you 10-15 hours of play-time. It's up to you if you want to pay the price. However on steam sales if it gets lower than $5, try it."
